{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic"]]},"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","externalID":"c:@M@OUDSTokensSemantic@objc(cs)MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","symbolKind":"class","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","roleHeading":"Class","modules":[{"name":"OUDSTokensSemantic"}]},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/init(_:)","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/init(compact:regular:)"],"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/compact","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/regular"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/fontToken(for:)","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/isEqual(_:)"],"anchor":"Instance-Methods","title":"Instance Methods"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["        \/\/ Assuming in Figma with have a font semantic token typeDisplayLarge,","        \/\/ with values depending to size class. These values are defined as font composite raw tokens.","        let typeBold850 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: fontSize850, lineHeight: fontLineHeight1050, weight: fontWeight700, letterSpacing: fontLetterSpacing850)","        let typeBold1450 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: fontSize1450, lineHeight: fontLineHeight1850, weight: fontWeight700, letterSpacing: fontLetterSpacing1450)","","        \/\/ Then the develoment team declares an \"higher\" level font semantic token","        \/\/ inside FontCompositeSemanticTokens protocol,","        \/\/ and defined inside OUDSTheme+FontCompositeSemanticTokens extension","        var typeDisplayLarge: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens {","            MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(compact: FontRawTokens.typeBold850, regular: FontRawTokens.typeBold1450)","        }","","        \/\/ If the same font is used whatever the size class is","        var typeDisplayLarge: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens { MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(FontRawTokens.typeBold650) }","","        \/\/ The theme exposes both generated elevation semantic tokens and \"crafted\" higher level elevation semantic tokens.","        \/\/ It is recommended to use the higher level version as it is less error-prone."]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The case of this "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is quite particular because in fact it contains "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FontCompositeRawToken"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(i.e. raw tokens) instead of semantic tokens."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In fact there is not “font composite semantic tokens” defined in the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" kit."}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.8.0"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Since"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Kind of semantic tokens which will wrap a combination of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FontCompositeRawToken"},{"text":" depending to size classes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Kind of composite token with multiple values, but not named “composite” because this word is already used in the design system.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Allows to gather the multiple-value tokens from ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}]},{"text":" inside one object.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If a font token exists with its value depending to the size class, it must be packed in such ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(cs)NSObject"],"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(pl)NSObject","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s7CVarArgP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s28CustomDebugStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SQ","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SH","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s8SendableP"],"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multiplefontcompositerawtokens"]}],"references":{"doc://OUDSTokensSemantic/documentation/OU